* {{IconSet|false|WARNING}}
** The tests were created with the help of AI. And thereby a security vulnerability was found
** This should probably be fixed in our fork
** Below is the long explanation and an AI prompt for improvement
** '''Problem Description'''
*** Proof of concept : test B4 on [[Dev/wikitest#CSS_Extension_Fork|CSS Extension Fork]] demonstrates the bypass: <code><nowiki>{{#css:/src-copy/%2e%2e/%2e%2e/COPYING}}</nowiki></code> produces a valid <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> tag instead of the expected "Invalid/malicious path" error.
*** In detail: The CSS Extension's path sanitizer fails to decode URL-encoded characters before performing security checks. The function <code>cssRender()</code> in <code>hooks.php</code> currently decodes only <code>%2f</code> (slash) and <code>%5c</code> (backslash) via <code>str_ireplace()</code>, but does '''not''' decode other percent-encoded characters like <code>%2e</code> (dot). This allows an attacker to bypass the path traversal protection by encoding <code>..</code> as <code>%2e%2e</code>. The subsequent <code>urlUtils->expand()</code> check then evaluates the still-encoded path, which does not contain literal <code>..</code> sequences, and therefore fails to detect the traversal attempt. Although nginx correctly decodes the URL when serving the request, the CSS Extension should block such paths at the application level before they reach the web server.
** '''Recommended Fix''' :
*** Add <code>rawurldecode()</code> to the path variable at the beginning of the file-based CSS branch in <code>cssRender()</code>, before the existing <code>str_ireplace()</code> calls. This ensures all percent-encoded characters are decoded prior to path normalization and security checks.
*** AI Prompt for Code Fix: {{CodeSelect|code=
The following PHP code from a MediaWiki extension has a security vulnerability:
URL-encoded path traversal via %2e (dot) is not detected because only %2f and
%5c are decoded before path validation.

File: hooks.php, method: cssRender()
Location: The "Regular file" branch, approximately line 130-140

Current code snippet:
$path = str_ireplace( '%2f', '/', $css );
$path = str_ireplace( '%5c', '\\', $path );
$path = str_replace( '\\', '/', $path );

Add rawurldecode() to decode ALL percent-encoded characters before these
replacements, so that %2e becomes '.' and the subsequent urlUtils->expand()
check can detect path traversal attempts. The fixed code should decode the
path first, then apply the existing replacements and validation.

Please provide the corrected PHP code snippet with a comment explaining the fix.
}}

